               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp> instrumentum textorium, secundum Ludolfum <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> radius textorius </quote></cit>, quo subtegmen stamini inseritur [cfr. amh. <foreign xml:lang="gez">መን፡</foreign> „the reed on a weaver’s loom, where the threads of the web pass through“, <ref cRef="Isenb." loc="31">Isenb. p. 31</ref>]. Legitur in homilia Procli in <ref cRef="Cyr." loc="119 ">Cyr. f. 119 </ref>(<cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> Mansi </quote></cit> Concil. <ref cRef="IV." loc="577 ">IV. 577 </ref>et 579): <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡ ምእናም፡ ግሩም፡ ዘቦቱ፡ ተአንመ፡ ዘሥጋዌሁ፡ ዕፁብ፡ ልብሰቱ፡ ወገባሪሁ፡</foreign> (<foreign xml:lang="grc">ἱστουργός</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወምሕኑ፡</foreign> (<foreign xml:lang="grc">ἔριθος</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘእምልዑል፡ ጽላሎተ፡ ኀይል፡ ወስፍሑ፡</foreign> (<foreign xml:lang="grc">ἔριον</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘእምጥንተ፡</foreign> (sic! <foreign xml:lang="grc">κώδιον</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሥጋሁ፡ ለአዳም፡ ወፋእሙ፡</foreign> (<foreign xml:lang="grc">κρόκη</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘእምድንግል፡ ንጹሕ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወመሥቄሁ፡</foreign> (<foreign xml:lang="grc">κερκίς</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸጋሁ፡ ለዘለብሶ፡ ወኬንያሁሰ፡</foreign> (<foreign xml:lang="grc">τεχνίτης</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቃል፡</foreign> Hoc simile a Proclo de Maria dictum in varios Aethiopum libros translatum legitur, <lbl expand="exempli gratia">ex. gr.</lbl> <ref cRef="Lit." loc="170,">Lit. f. 170,</ref> 3. [Denominatum videtur a <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> percutiendo </quote></cit> et sicut <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἡ κερκίς</foreign> primitus <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> pectinem </quote></cit> (alias <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἡ σπάθη</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="gez">መሥቄ፡</foreign>), deinde <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> radium textorium </quote></cit> significasse]. </sense>
               
